<DATE>951227</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Ecstasy charge</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>2</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974684177</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A man appeared in court yesterday in connection with the discovery of ecstasy
tablets worth #500,000. Christopher Major, 22, of Cronton, Merseyside, was
charged with possession of a controlled drug with intent to supply. He was
remanded in custody until January 3 by Huyton magistrates.
