<HEADLINE>Woman, 83, critical after attack in street</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974684213</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
AN 83-year-old woman was last night unconscious and critically ill in hospital
after being found in the street after a vicious attack.
Mrs Evelyn Stanford, 83, was discovered lying on the pavement about a half a
mile from her home in Wrekin Drive, Wolverhampton, early yesterday.
Detective Inspector Philip Thompson said: ``We are very concerned for her.
``We don't know what she was doing out at that time of night.
``She was seen by a witness minutes before she was attacked. When he returned
she was lying on the ground being tended by a passer-by.''
The witness had noted she was carrying a bag but it had gone when she was found
lying on the pavement on Goldthorn Hill just after midnight.
Detective Inspector Thompson said: ``She had spent part of Christmas Day with
her family but we don't know if she then visited someone else.
``We need to know her movements before she was attacked.''
She has been unconscious at the Royal Hospital in Wolverhampton with serious
head injuries since the attack.
</TEXT>
