<TEXT>
Man charged
A MAN was remanded in custody for three days yesterday when he appeared before
magistrates at Berwick charged with attempted arson. Martin Burgin, 44, of
Cheviot View, Ponteland, was alleged to have committed the offence at Nursery
Cottage, Chatton, near Wooler, on Christmas Eve.
Cut free
FIREFIGHTERS had to use cutting gear to release passenger Elizabeth Fairley,
81, of Duns, after ing a two-car crash on the A1 Berwick Bypass. She was taken
to Berwick Infirmary suffering from leg injuries but later released.
