<HEADLINE>Fake it and make it wild</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>John Davidson</BYLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>18</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>features</ARTICLETYPE>
<GRAPHIC>photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>974684305</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
lunacy is the
friend of the
faux, as fake
furs become
unashamedly
ludicrous.
John Davidson
visits a fantasy
island of
foxy dreams
ONCE upon a time, it was a nasty evil thing. The fake fur coat, that is - so
unconvincing, in bands of over-coloured static bristle. It tried and tried to
look real: impersonating mink, trying to appear foxy. Yet, somehow it only ever
resembled a vulgar car-seat cover. And that was before kitsch seemed in any way
cute. No ice princess would have been caught frost-bitten in such a garment. At
all those great occasions in her snow-covered realm, nothing but the real thing
would ever have done.
But in these ever-so-nice nineties, we are increasingly obliged to be caring,
concerned, and kind to wee furry animals. Reality, in these times, most
certainly bites. So what is an ice princess to choose for the trappings of
contemporary glamour? There is a new breed of hairy beast on the loose: the
fantasy fur coat, developed from a surprisingly luxurious strain of acrylic
pile fabrics.
Just as attitudes to fur have changed, so has the way we fake it. Sometimes it
still apes those wilder reaches of reality - almost literally, of course, when
the fur being mimicked is monkey. But more often, today's high fashion faux
furs are as unashamedly ludicrous as they are gorgeous, glamorous and glorious.
For they revel in their obvious fakery; they represent an art of the
all-but-impossible by appearing about as unlikely a pelt as possible.
The ultimate coat? For this festive season, our own ice princess chose one,
long and white - as abominable as the mythical Yeti, yet silken to the touch.
Or another, short and rather sporty, raggedly curled like the fleece of a
Mongolian lamb on E. And like all good fairy tales, these are only
make-believe. Everyone (except perhaps those little acryls) can live happily
ever after.
</TEXT>
