<BYLINE>DUNCAN WEST</BYLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>24</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974684310</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BASKETBALL
THE ill-fated Scottish Cup second-round tie between City of Aberdeen Leopards
and Glasgow Brightsiders will now not take place at all.
Instead, Brightsiders have been placed in the quarter-finals as Leopards were
deemed to have defaulted by not playing by the due date.
The tie should have been played by the last weekend in November, but was
rearranged for the following Saturday. It was then postponed because the clubs
could not agree a tip-off time.
They rearranged again for December 16, but no referee was available, partly due
to the Boroughmuir Invitation Tournament in Edinburgh from which Glasgow
withdrew to play the cup match.
Now the SBA has awarded the tie to Glasgow, who will be at home to Boroughmuir
at Easterhouse Sports Centre on January 21.
Glasgow are due to play Edzell Enforcers at Edzell on January 6 in their first
match in the league play-offs.
Paisley will be at home to champions Livingston Bulls in the other match of the
championship section of five with Edinburgh Burger Kings having a bye.
DUNCAN WEST
</TEXT>
