<HEADLINE>`Strong squads' are left dazed</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>22</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<GRAPHIC>Photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>974684328</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
I HAVE just read Ken Gallacher's article on Mark McGhee and, as an exiled
Reading supporter, I am a little bit nonplussed by his blase attitude that
``club loyalty is only for the fans.''
Does he realise that McGhee is held in contempt and regarded as a pariah by all
and sundry at Elm Park?
Once he has ground-hopped to the next club after Wolverhampton Wanderers,
enticed by more money, he may one day look back and see that, although in each
club he has indeed left a ``strong squad,'' he has also left them dazed,
confused and very, very angry by his mercenary attitude to football.
But as long as the money keeps rolling in Mr McGhee, do not worry, you can just
put up a big wall around your house and forget all about us.
Andrew W Smith,
2067 Dumbarton Road,
Yoker,
Glasgow.
</TEXT>
