<DATE>951227</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Crossed wires</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>22</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>974684342</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THIS might be termed a ``Dear John'' letter. Your rugby columnist John Beattie
appears not only to lack the sense of humour essential to his job but also sees
almost anyone as fair game, especially if they display dedication to the
administration of the game of rugby.
How else could he completely misconstrue in his Diary comment of December 21
the pawky Scots humour so splendidly displayed by Glasgow District's Tom
Morrice in his recent radio interview. Come on, John, get with it!
Stuart M Wallace,
186 Eastwoodmains Road,
Clarkston.
